{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592679","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592679"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:18:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:18:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15273"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15273"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0.85,0.07,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7964"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65215"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7964","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7964"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15273"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50652"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1044"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"8746"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19381"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19384"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21671"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65215","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65215"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIt is estimated that in Australia about 1 - 70 individuals have coeliac disease, yet only about 20% of these will have sufficient symptoms to get the diagnosis considered and established.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Diagnosis can be confirmed while on a gluten-free diet","Diagnosis can be made on serology alone","Duodenal biopsy is the gold standard for diagnosis","Genetic testing is required for diagnosis","Skin biopsy is necessary for diagnosis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe diagnosis of coeliac disease requires multiple elements working together:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerology alone\u003C/strong\u003E is insufficient for diagnosis, though it is an important screening tool\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuodenal biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E showing characteristic villous atrophy remains the gold standard for diagnosis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenetic testing\u003C/strong\u003E may support diagnosis but is not required and cannot confirm the condition\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETesting must be performed while on a \u003Cstrong\u003Egluten-containing diet\u003C/strong\u003E as both serology and histology normalise on a gluten-free diet\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESkin biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E is only relevant for diagnosing dermatitis herpetiformis, a condition associated with coeliac disease, but is not used to diagnose coeliac disease itself\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is essential that patients continue to consume gluten during the diagnostic process to avoid false negative results.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Coeliac disease diagnosis requires positive serology and duodenal biopsy while on a gluten-containing diet","Small intestinal biopsy showing villous atrophy is the gold standard for diagnosing coeliac disease","Gluten must be present in the diet for accurate diagnostic testing in suspected coeliac disease"],"references":["DuPont HL. Persistent Diarrhea: A Clinical Review. JAMA. 2016 Jun 28;315(24):2712-23. doi: 10.1001/jama.2016.7833. PMID: 27357241","Nemeth V, Pfleghaar N. Diarrhea. [Updated 2022 Nov 21]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK448082/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50652"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15273"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50652","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50652"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T21:18:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-25T21:19:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7964"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65215"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6